Careers

Careers






Your browser's Javascript functionality is turned off. Please turn it on so that you can experience the full capabilities of this site.




Working at Black Diamond
Bound by our undying passion for climbing, skiing and mountain adventure, Black Diamond Equipment employees number more than 500 worldwide. That same passion is what drives us to relentlessly design, engineer and build the world's best climbing, skiing and mountain equipment. Working at Black Diamond Equipment allows for a career that aligns with and integrates the human-powered pursuits that we all live by. Explore a career that aligns with your passions.

Careers
We're always on the lookout for talented and passionate people to join our team. We offer a wide range of careers at our headquarters and distribution center, both located in Salt Lake City, Utah.
Find All Jobs

HIRING PROCESS
The following information will give you a better understanding of how the hiring process works for US-based jobs at Black Diamond Equipment.
Apply Online
To see an updated list of our job postings, click the "Find All Jobs" button above. If you find a position that you are interested in and qualified for, you can click the "Apply Now" button found at the end of the posting. If this is your first time applying at Black Diamond, you will be prompted to complete a profile, upload a resume and answer a few questions. If you are a returning applicant who would like to apply for an open position, at the top of the job posting will be a link for "Returning Applicants." Here you can apply for the job and update your profile information.
All applicants must go through the Online Application Process. We do not accept walk-in applicants. We also are unable to process resumes sent via mail, fax or email.
We Contact You
After you have successfully applied for an open position online, Black Diamond Equipment will send you an email notification, advising you that we have received your information and that nothing further is required from you. (Please make sure you check your SPAM folder as sometimes the notifications can be filtered into it.)
How We Interview
Depending on the position, either Human Resources or the hiring manager for the position will keep you informed regarding the status of your application. You may be asked to interview via phone and/or in person. We look forward to reviewing your application and wish you the best in your job search.

BENEFITS
At Black Diamond Equipment we offer employees and their eligible dependents a wide range of benefits. Some of these benefits include:

• Medical and Dental Insurance
• Company-funded Life Insurance
• Company-funded Disability Insurance
• Supplemental Life Insurance
• Supplemental Dependent Life Insurance
• Supplemental Accident Insurance
• 401k with company match
• Vacation Time and Sick Time
• Holiday Pay
• Employee Assistance Program
• Retail Discounts
• Dog-friendly workplace
• Benefit eligibility varies according to employment status.

 

LIVING IN UTAH
The Wasatch Front of Utah offers nearly unlimited outdoor opportunities for Black Diamond Equipment employees. Multiple world-class ski areas and vast backcountry terrain with an average yearly snowfall of 500 inches make pre-work skiing (aka, dawn patrols) a regular occurrence. The canyons of Big Cottonwood, Little Cottonwood and American Fork offer thousands of rock and ice routes, and the red rock deserts of Moab and southern Utah are popular weekend destinations. Lunchtime rides and runs are had on dozens of trails within minutes of Black Diamond Equipment headquarters.
In addition to the unparalleled outdoor opportunities, Salt Lake City is home to ample cultural diversions, such as great restaurants, bars, theater, art and live music. Unique neighborhood districts, bike-friendly streets and low average home prices also contribute to Salt Lake City's laid-back appeal.
Check out the following sites for more info:

• Utah Newcomers Guide
