Black Diamond, Inc. Key Developments

Black Diamond Mulls Acquisitions
Jun 15 17
Black Diamond, Inc. (NasdaqGS:BDE) is looking for acquisitions. The company from time to time intends to make an offering up to 7,500,000 shares of its common stock, in connection with the acquisition of assets, stock or businesses, whether
by purchase, merger or any other form of business combination.


Black Diamond, Inc. Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017; Provides Earnings Guidance for the Fiscal Year 2017
May 8 17
Black Diamond, Inc. reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported total sales of $41,556,000 against $38,207,000 a year ago. Sales in the first quarter of 2017 increased 9% to $41.6 million compared to $38.2 million in the same year-ago quarter. The increase was due to strong growth across each of the different product categories of climb, mountain, and ski. Sales were also up in every channel and geographic region. Foreign exchange had a minimal impact on the first quarter. Operating loss was $276,000 against $3,873,000 a year ago. Loss before income tax was $1,245,000 against $4,151,000 a year ago. Net loss was $1,455,000 or $0.05 per basic and diluted share against $4,013,000 or $0.13 per basic and diluted share a year ago. EBITDA was $548,000 against LBITDA of $2,986,000 a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was $622,000 against adjusted LBITDA of $2,352,000 a year ago.

For the fiscal year 2017, the company expects sales to grow between 3%-7% to approximately $153 to $158 million compared to $148.2 million in 2016. On a constant currency basis, the company expects sales to range between $154 to $159 million, or up 4%-7% compared to 2016. The company continues to expect gross margin in fiscal 2017 to increase approximately 300 to 400 basis points and range between 32.5%-33.5% compared to 29.5% in 2016. The company also continues to expect selling, general and administrative costs, including approximately $4.5 million of cash corporate overhead expenditures, to be approximately $50.5 million compared to $49.9 million in 2016. The company expects approximately $2.5 million in capital expenditures in 2017.


Black Diamond, Inc. Announces Resignation of Robert Schiller from Board of Directors
May 1 17
Black Diamond, Inc. announced that, effective May 01, 2017, Robert Schiller has resigned as executive vice chairman and director in order to pursue other interests.


